    "name": "Monte Carlo global sensitivity analysis for VAD hemolysis prediction",
    "description": "A Sobol-index Monte Carlo sensitivity analysis was performed over 10,000 samples varying blood viscosity (±15%), pump rotational speed (±3%), inlet flow rate (±8%), red blood cell mechanical threshold stress (±20%), and turbulence model closure coefficients (±10%). Hemolysis index variance was dominated by the RBC mechanical threshold stress parameter (first-order Sobol index 0.41) and turbulence model coefficients (0.28), with rotational speed contributing 0.19; viscosity and flow rate together accounted for the remaining 0.12, confirming that constitutive model uncertainty is the primary driver of prediction uncertainty at MRL 5 operating conditions.",
    "method": "Sobol quasi-random Monte Carlo",
    "sampleSize": 10000,
    "dominantFactors": [
      "RBC mechanical threshold stress",
      "turbulence model closure coefficients",
      "pump rotational speed"
    ]
  },
